Response to
Episode 1 - "Standing Up in the Milky Way"
@-------------------------------------------------
This was actually SO FREAKING COOL!!!! The visuals were really cool and I was just in awe the entire time! The calendar also kind of shook me because everything that really happened in our world only occurred in the last, minute or so?! But overall, I really enjoyed it. Although I have different views as Tyson on some stuff, I learned a lot and developed a slight interest in this! I also liked the small, inspiring commentary that he makes throughout the entire episode, especially how we, humans, had to learn that we weren't the center anymore but that we had to work together. It's the little things that matter the most, like how that one inch allowed our whole entire galaxy/system to be formed, or how just one message from the scientist changed Tyson's perspective. I also learned that the scientific method was one of the greatest things invented, because it allows us to reject bad ideas, explore, discover, and try out new ideas.
-------------------------------------------------@


