Response to
Episode 10 - "The Electric Boy"
@-------------------------------------------------
I really enjoyed this one too! Michael's Faraday story was really interesting, and it showed that if you put your mind to it, you can do it. I also learned that small things matter, just like how his few years at the glass factory helped him solve the mystery and the connection between the magnet, electricity and light. I also learned that education is important, because although Faraday showed all these cool electricity and magnet related things, people could not fully agree with him becuase Faraday could not prove it mathematically. Overall, these few episodes were super interesting and I'm definitely positive that I might watch a few more! 
